==Trivia==
*In the comics, Agatha Harkness is a witch who lived through the fall of [[Atlantis]] and the {{WPS|Salem witch trials}}. She was a mentor to [[Scarlet Witch]] and the babysitter of [[Franklin Richards]]. In the Ultimate Universe, she was a foe of the Ultimate [[Fantastic Four]], able to split from one individual to seven.
*Agnes' fake marriage anniversary with her husband [[Ralph Bohner|Ralph]] (June 2nd), references June 2nd 1692, the day the Salem witch trials began.
*In the Marvel Cinematic Universe, Agatha Harkness was the inspiration behind Dolly Parton's 1973 hit "Jolene", and was even slapped by the country music star in 1972.{{Ref|AAA106}}{{Ref|Jolene}}
*Harkness' outfit on the [[Witches' Road]] is meant to symbolize a crow, having many details like the end of the coat looking like a tail. Additionally, inside the coat, there are runes.{{Ref|TMoAAA}}
* Kathryn Hahn stated in a German interview that Agatha loves whoever she loves regardless of gender, indicating that she is attracted to multiple genders.<ref>[https://www.moviepilot.de/news/liebe-ist-liebe-kathryn-hahn-feiert-im-interview-zu-agatha-all-along-den-queeren-twist-der-marvel-serie-1149298 Kathryn Hahn feiert im Interview zu Agatha All Along den queeren Twist der Marvel-Serie]</ref>

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Kathryn Hahn]] was secretly informed since the beginning that she would be playing Agatha Harkness in ''[[WandaVision]]''. To prepare for the role, Hahn read some comic books featuring her character and saw other movies of the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dbYNo8QwbLE Kathryn Hahn Reacts to WandaVision’s "Agatha All Along" Topping the iTunes Charts]</ref>
*In the early development stages of ''[[WandaVision]]'', Harkness served more like a mentor figure towards [[Wanda Maximoff]], but the crew realized that making her a proper antagonist would serve the show's structure well as they legitimately broke the episodes. The possibility of Harkness wanting Maximoff's powers to bring her [[Evanora Harkness|mother]] back was also explored.<ref>[https://www.etonline.com/wandavision-series-finale-interview-jac-schaeffer-161951 'WandaVision' Creator on Agatha's Master Plan, That Ralph Bohner Reveal and White Vision (Exclusive)]</ref> Back when Harkness was planned to be Maximoff's mentor, she was going to teach her early on a binding spell Maximoff would use while saying goodbye for the last time to [[Vision]] in the [[The Series Finale|final episode]].<ref>[https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/tv-features/oral-history-wandavision-olsen-bettany-hahn-feige-1155120/ The Oral History of ‘WandaVision’]</ref>
*[[Whitney Coleman]], [[Athena Perample]] and [[Mary Pat Letourneau]] were stunt doubles for [[Kathryn Hahn]] in the role of Agatha Harkness.

